1
00:00:08,291 --> 00:00:09,958
[LUNAR] ♪ My heart
beats a symphony, ♪

2
00:00:10,041 --> 00:00:11,666
♪ Your love inspires me, ♪

3
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:14,750
♪ That's how I know
I'll be with you one day ♪

4
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:18,041
♪ No matter how far our hearts
will never stay apart, ♪

5
00:00:18,125 --> 00:00:23,125
♪ Your love pulls
me close to you ♪

6
00:00:23,208 --> 00:00:27,291
♪ It's your gravitation! ♪

7
00:00:29,791 --> 00:00:31,000
[ANNOUNCER]
That was Lunar with her

8
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:33,083
heart stopping single
"Gravitation."

9
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:35,500
Thank you, everybody!

10
00:00:36,416 --> 00:00:38,625
[Lunar laughs]

11
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:40,958
[LUNAR THINKS] Everyone
adores our songs.

12
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,750
What a wonderful feeling!

13
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,208
[CROWD] Lunar!

14
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:46,500
I love you, Lunar!

15
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:49,958
[LUNAR THINKS]
That's right, humans.

16
00:00:50,041 --> 00:00:53,208
Bow down before
the power of our songs.

17
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,416
[NARRATOR]
Beneath the gently rolling

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,500
waves of the Seto Inland Sea.

19
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:04,166
Young Nagasumi's life is saved,
and forever changed.

20
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:07,958
But as with any debt,
this one too must be repaid.

21
00:01:08,041 --> 00:01:09,833
So our story begins.

22
00:01:09,916 --> 00:01:14,333
Please humor them with a smile,
for young love is never easy.

23
00:01:16,916 --> 00:01:21,875
♪

24
00:02:50,625 --> 00:02:54,000
[Lunar laughs insanely]

25
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:56,000
[LUNAR] They were hypnotized
by our songs yet again.

26
00:02:56,083 --> 00:02:58,208
Yes, pathetic humans,
that's right, worship us.

27
00:02:58,291 --> 00:02:59,208
Bow down.

28
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:00,833
[KAMATA] Very good
work today, Lunar!

29
00:03:00,916 --> 00:03:03,875
Yes? Oh, well thank
you very much!

30
00:03:03,958 --> 00:03:05,125
[LUNAR] Oh.

31
00:03:05,208 --> 00:03:06,875
It's just my manager,
and not an adoring fan.

32
00:03:06,958 --> 00:03:08,458
At least knock next
time, would ya?

33
00:03:08,541 --> 00:03:09,875
Lunar, you have
a full schedule

34
00:03:09,958 --> 00:03:11,458
of commercials and
recording tomorrow,

35
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:12,750
so try to get to
bed early tonight.

36
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,708
You do need your sleep.

37
00:03:14,791 --> 00:03:15,958
Yeah.

38
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:17,708
And, honey, one
other thing as well.

39
00:03:17,791 --> 00:03:19,166
It's just something
that the don, uh,

40
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:21,458
something that the
company president told me.

41
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:22,666
[LUNAR] Papa, huh?

42
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,208
[KAMATA] That friend
of yours from childhood.

43
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:27,333
What was her name again?
Oh, yes, Sun from the Seto gang.

44
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:29,750
Well, it seems she's
moved to Saitama.

45
00:03:29,833 --> 00:03:30,791
Maybe it would
be good for you

46
00:03:30,875 --> 00:03:32,250
to pay her a visit
sometime soon.

47
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:34,583
Wouldn't you like to say 'hi'
to your old friend, Lunar?

48
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:35,791
[ LUNA] Kamata,
I need you to cancel

49
00:03:35,875 --> 00:03:37,583
all of my appointments
for tomorrow.

50
00:03:37,666 --> 00:03:39,208
Yes, of course.

51
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:42,458
[KAMATA] Wait, Lunar,
what's gotten into you?

52
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:45,833
Sun Seto.

53
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:48,625
[LUNA (YOUNG)]
♪ This is not the way ♪

54
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:52,916
♪ romance is
supposed to be. ♪

55
00:03:53,583 --> 00:03:59,125
♪ Love is worth the risk 'cause
we have nothing left to lose. ♪

56
00:03:59,208 --> 00:04:04,166
♪ Think of everything
love gives us in return! ♪

57
00:04:05,416 --> 00:04:06,791
[LUNAR (YOUNG)]
Thank you!

58
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,750
Bye now!

59
00:04:13,166 --> 00:04:14,666
[Lunar laughs]

60
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,750
[LUNAR (YOUNG)] A mermaid's
true weapon is her voice.

61
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:17,958
Her sweet song.

62
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:19,541
A good voice is the
greatest badge of pride,

63
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:21,291
and there is no mermaid
anywhere out there

64
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:24,041
who can sing better
than Lunar Edomae!

65
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,125
[WAITRESS]
Don't know what it is,

66
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,833
but that kid's got
one creepy laugh.

67
00:04:27,916 --> 00:04:29,625
[MOBSTER A]
There's another girl singing.

68
00:04:29,708 --> 00:04:30,916
Listen to her.

69
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,875
[SUN (YOUNG)]
♪ Momotaro-san, Momotaro-san ♪

70
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,875
♪ Can you share
your dumplings? ♪

71
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:39,166
♪ Will you share
them with me? ♪

72
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:39,958
[MOBSTER B]
I don't understand what

73
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:41,416
this girl is doing to me.

74
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:44,000
I can't stop crying.

75
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:47,416
Yeah, it's tearin' at some
wound deep inside'a me.

76
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,083
Her voice is so sweet
and innocent I can't take it.

77
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,750
I'll share them
with you dear little Sun.

78
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,125
Maybe we should
all try to be more

79
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:56,750
like that and
share our dumplings.

80
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,958
[MOBSTER A] I've
never heard another

81
00:04:58,041 --> 00:05:00,583
child sing as well
as Lunar before.

82
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:04,625
[MOBSTER B] And the winner
of tonight's singing contest is,

83
00:05:04,708 --> 00:05:07,291
Sun from the Seto gang!

84
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:09,291
Someone who
thinks they can

85
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:11,416
sing better than us
cannot be tolerated.

86
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:14,083
We'll teach you, Sun Seto.

87
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:17,375
[SARU] I can't believe Sun made
us go home without her.

88
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:18,708
This sucks.

89
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,333
She said that
she was going to

90
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:22,166
be helping out the class rep,
so we just have to accept it.

91
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:23,958
And you didn't volunteer
to help them out?

92
00:05:24,041 --> 00:05:26,250
Nah, they said they were setting
up for tomorrow's health class.

93
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,833
Now that I wouldn't
mind helping with.

94
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:29,000
Think of all
the cool secrets you

95
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:30,583
could learn about
girls' bodies there.

96
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:32,875
Oh, I almost forgot.

97
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:34,458
[SARU] Holy freaking
crap on a stick!

98
00:05:34,541 --> 00:05:36,291
This is a Lunar souvenir that
you can only get at concerts!

99
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:38,250
[SARU] B-But how
did you get this? How?

100
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,625
[NAGASUMI] Oh,
I got it yesterday when I

101
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:41,583
went to watch her
tape a concert for tv.

102
00:05:41,666 --> 00:05:42,416
You mean you
won a ticket?

103
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,958
No one gets those!

104
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:45,083
Do you know how lucky you are?
You have been truly blessed.

105
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,041
Are you a unicorn?

106
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:47,333
You can keep
that little token,

107
00:05:47,416 --> 00:05:48,375
you poor schmuck who didn't

108
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:50,375
get to see Lunar
performing live.

109
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:51,375
You think maybe
you're letting

110
00:05:51,458 --> 00:05:52,833
this go to your head, huh, kid?

111
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:54,000
She sings so well, but she's

112
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:56,000
got such an amazing
personality, too.

113
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,416
I know! She's so
sweet and humble

114
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,083
in the face of
her great success.

115
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:00,708
I'm going to her
next concert, also.

116
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:02,250
And I'll have a
good seat this time!

117
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,916
Now, you hold
on a second there.

118
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,166
Should you be
saying that...?

119
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:07,250
After all, what would
Sun think about it, huh?

120
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,666
[SARU] You're living
with a girl that cute,

121
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,750
and your eye's still roaming?
Is she not enough for you?

122
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,500
It has nothing to
do with Sun.

123
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:15,041
No? I beg to differ.

124
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:17,583
Sun is a real girl, and Lunar
is a famous pop star.

125
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:19,250
You can't possibly
equate the two.

126
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:20,333
Oh, I see how it is,

127
00:06:20,416 --> 00:06:21,791
so you've rationalized
your betrayal.

128
00:06:21,875 --> 00:06:24,250
What a thoughtful guy
you are, Nagasumi.

129
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,958
Where did all this
rain come from?

130
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:30,750
[SARU] See ya.
I'm gonna go home now.

131
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:32,583
Yeah, okay.
I'll see you later.

132
00:06:37,541 --> 00:06:39,083
[NAGASUMI] What's that?

133
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,875
[NAGASUMI] Hey!
Are you all right, miss?

134
00:06:40,958 --> 00:06:42,958
Can I help?
What happened to you--

135
00:06:45,458 --> 00:06:46,958
That's not a fish!

136
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,916
It's a mermaid collapsed in the
street who I don't even know!

137
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,291
[LUNAR] Stupid rain storm
came out of nowhere!

138
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:53,416
Oh good, so she's alive.

139
00:06:54,208 --> 00:06:56,166
L-l-l-l-lu!

140
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,041
You saw me!

141
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,958
The random mermaid
is really Lunar!

142
00:07:00,041 --> 00:07:03,416
[LUNAR] No!

143
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,541
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
This is insane!

144
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:05,916
What is Lunar
doing here?

145
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,875
Okay, better question,
Lunar's a mermaid?

146
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:12,875
[NAGASUMI] That was a
mermaid ultrasonic wave attack.

147
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:14,625
We're impressed you
know something like that.

148
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:15,666
What's going on?

149
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,291
You okay? The rain
came so sudden.

150
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:19,625
What you say Miss Lunar.
Did this human see something?

151
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:21,166
[LUNAR] He saw our true form.

152
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:24,000
Bob, Michael, we'll need to
take the human back with us.

153
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:25,000
Yes, Miss Lunar.

154
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:26,000
Not good.

155
00:07:27,250 --> 00:07:29,333
I remember being
kidnapped like this before.

156
00:07:29,416 --> 00:07:30,250
Um, uh.

157
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,166
What is it?

158
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,500
Should I assume
that I'm going

159
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,375
to be killed now that I've
seen your mermaid form?

160
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:36,083
My you do
catch on quickly.

161
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:37,958
[NAGASUMI THINKS] Why does
this keep happening to me?

162
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,333
[SUN] Stop it now.

163
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,541
[SUN] Yer talkin'
about horrible stuff

164
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:44,625
like killin' right in front
of my own house?

165
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:48,083
So now what's
all the fuss about?

166
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,958
My, the rain stopped
as suddenly as it started.

167
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,041
Long time no see.
Sun Seto.

168
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:01,750
I recognize you.
You're Lunar Edomae!

169
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:02,875
[LUNAR] That's right.

170
00:08:02,958 --> 00:08:04,708
Your fearsome rival,
your arch nemesis,

171
00:08:04,791 --> 00:08:06,541
the famous singer Lunar Edomea

172
00:08:06,625 --> 00:08:08,166
has come to pay
you a visit, Sun.

173
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:09,666
[SUN] Wow, it's been
so long, Lunar!

174
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:11,416
Don't hug
us so familiarly!

175
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,166
So, when the hell
did you arrive here?

176
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:16,208
A respectful mermaid would've
come to see us long before now!

177
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:17,583
[SUN] Oh... sorry.

178
00:08:17,666 --> 00:08:20,000
Lots of stuff happened,
and I kinda forgot about ya.

179
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,916
Ooh look! It's the
pretty little singer

180
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,750
from the yakuza
singing contests.

181
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,166
[SUN] Give back
Nagasumi now, please.

182
00:08:26,250 --> 00:08:28,791
Oh yes,
of course, here.

183
00:08:32,125 --> 00:08:33,041
I'll have you
know that we

184
00:08:33,125 --> 00:08:34,416
never once forgot
about you, Sun!

185
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,083
We remember what you did to us!

186
00:08:36,166 --> 00:08:37,000
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
This girl's a bit different

187
00:08:37,083 --> 00:08:38,875
from the Lunar that I've seen.

188
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,750
You certainly seem used
to drying off tails, human.

189
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:44,958
[NAGASUMI]
You have no idea.

190
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:46,375
[Sun groans]

191
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:49,000
[LUNAR] Now there's something
I'd like to know about.

192
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,458
What sort of
relationship do

193
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:53,500
you have with this human?

194
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:57,291
[LUNAR] He saw your fins
so you agreed to marry him?

195
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,708
Impossible!
How could a noble

196
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:01,958
mermaid agree to
marry a lowly human?

197
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,375
[SUN] But there's
a really good story

198
00:09:03,458 --> 00:09:04,958
about a mermaid
marryin' a human.

199
00:09:05,041 --> 00:09:07,500
That story is fiction,
and it doesn't end well.

200
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,833
Why can't we get it over
with and kill him already?

201
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,000
Ya know, Lunar,
yer kinda mean.

202
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:14,000
That's exactly why Sun
took me into her family.

203
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:16,000
To avoid either
of us being killed.

204
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:17,708
Uh huh,
and your point is?

205
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:19,291
[NAGASUMI] So I won't
let you kill me, Lunar.

206
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:21,250
I'll do whatever I can
to stop you and I won't

207
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,875
go down without a fight.

208
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,333
I owe her that much.

209
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:27,000
My life belongs
completely to Sun now.

210
00:09:27,083 --> 00:09:28,875
Thank ya, Nagasumi.

211
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:31,083
[SUN] What is it?

212
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:33,500
[LUNAR THINKS] We lost to
Sun in the singing contests.

213
00:09:33,583 --> 00:09:35,708
Every single time.

214
00:09:35,791 --> 00:09:38,250
[LUNAR] To us,
singing was everything.

215
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:41,750
To her, singing was nothing
but silly nursery rhymes.

216
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:43,416
To prove that we
were better than Sun,

217
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,583
we dedicated our
lives to singing.

218
00:09:45,666 --> 00:09:47,958
We even entered the
entertainment industry

219
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:51,833
and struggled long and hard,
clawing our way to the top.

220
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:55,125
And when we came to her
to flaunt our musical success.

221
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:58,083
That girl.
That girl.

222
00:09:58,166 --> 00:10:01,666
She turns around and flaunts
this human boy in our face!

223
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:05,125
Why Sun? Why do
you always make us feel

224
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:07,875
bad about what
we don't have, huh?

225
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:10,625
What do you mean,
what you don't have?

226
00:10:10,708 --> 00:10:12,791
 In that case, Sun.
We'll take him.

227
00:10:12,875 --> 00:10:15,500
We'll take that
husband of yours.

228
00:10:15,583 --> 00:10:17,958
He saw us in our true
mermaid form, after all.

229
00:10:18,041 --> 00:10:20,833
His puny life is
our rightful property.

230
00:10:20,916 --> 00:10:23,875
Uh-oh. I don't
like this at all. Not good.

231
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:26,625
[LUNAR THINKS] That's right.
We'll steal Sun's happiness.

232
00:10:26,708 --> 00:10:28,166
You're ours, human!

233
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,000
Just imagine for
the rest of your life,

234
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:32,916
you'll be our personal
manservant, my darling boy.

235
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,500
Uh-oh... I don't think I like
the sound of that much, either.

236
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:38,000
[SUN] I'll teach ya to try
and take what's mine!

237
00:10:38,083 --> 00:10:41,166
I met Nagasumi a long
time before you did, Lunar.

238
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,250
You better back off right now!

239
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,750
Now, now it isn't a question
of chronology is it?

240
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,708
It doesn't matter
who caught him first.

241
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:50,916
We're just offering to help out.
We can protect him.

